{
  "text": "These insights have been flanked and supported by the successful experience of industrial districts, formalised in a model that identifies networking within a common production context, spatially defined within local geographical borders where actors share a common entrepreneurial, social and institutional background. Firms are all small and medium and are part of a complex system of relationships that implies a detailed division and specialisation of labour which improves the overall competitiveness of the district [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Porter, 1987 1 ; [CITATION_5] .",
